I make these all the time, to the delight of my friends and family... they beg me for them! I alter the recipe as follows: use the zest from one whole orange, use 1 1/4 cu of cranberries and chop them for a less chewy experience, lower the temperature to 350 because the bottoms tend to burn & adjust cooking time accordingly, use a (kitchenaid) mixer - much easier, make 2 rounds instead of 1 to make smaller scones, add a buttermilk wash and sprinkle with raw turbinado sugar. I've had good experiences freezing the unbaked dough (already cut into wedges, but without the wash & sugar) and baking what I needed at the time. Absolutely fantastic!

